==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''the triangle inequality''' (''[[uncountable]]'')
{{wikipedia}}
#{{analysis}} The [[inequality]] that states that the [[magnitude]] of the [[sum]] of two [[vector]]s is less than or equal to the sum of the magnitudes of the vectors, or any equivalent inequality in other [[space]]s.

